This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com.

When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:

My meme

my meme describes the comparison for morning mental outlook of myself and others

library(magick)

night <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQrt8NyarH8-7GKwuolAArzzk7MjJWZPXQXbw&usqp=CAU") %>%
  image_resize("500x500!")
morning <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRhX8bAbdfbIx-bnPOSQvkVdr9lGiTNH8JkMA&usqp=CAU") %>%
  image_resize("500x500!")

time_text1 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = "white") %>%
  
  image_annotate(text = 'my mental outlook at night',
                 color = "black",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

time_text2 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = "black") %>%
  
  image_annotate(text = 'my mental outlook at morning',
                 color = "white",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

top_row <- image_append(c(time_text1, night))
bottom_row <- image_append(c(time_text2, morning))

mental_outlook_meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(800)

mental_outlook_meme %>%
  image_write("my_meme.png")

My animation GIF My animation GIF is to show

library(magick)

night <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQrt8NyarH8-7GKwuolAArzzk7MjJWZPXQXbw&usqp=CAU") %>%
  image_resize("500x500!")
morning <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRhX8bAbdfbIx-bnPOSQvkVdr9lGiTNH8JkMA&usqp=CAU") %>%
  image_resize("500x500!")

time_text1 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = "white") %>%
  
  image_annotate(text = "my mental outlook\nat night",
                 color = "black",
                 size = 60,
                 gravity = "center")

time_text2 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = "black") %>%
  
  image_annotate(text = "my mental outlook\n at morning",
                 color = "white",
                 size = 60,
                 gravity = "center")

frame <- c(time_text1, night, time_text2, morning)
image_animate(frame, fps = 2)
